# ============================================
# VERCEL DEPLOYMENT - Environment Variables
# ============================================
# Set these in Vercel Dashboard
# Go to: Your Project → Settings → Environment Variables
# ============================================

# ⚠️ REQUIRED - Backend API URL
# This is your Render backend URL
# Get it from: Render dashboard → inventory-backend service
# Example: https://inventory-backend-xxxx.onrender.com
# NO trailing slash!
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://inventory-backend-xxxx.onrender.com

# ============================================
# OPTIONAL - Analytics & Monitoring
# ============================================

# Google Analytics (optional)
# Get from: https://analytics.google.com
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# Sentry for frontend error tracking (optional)
# Get from: https://sentry.io
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=https://xxxxx@xxxxx.ingest.sentry.io/xxxxx

# ============================================
# OPTIONAL - Feature Flags
# ============================================

# Enable/disable features
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ENABLE_ANALYTICS=true
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ENABLE_SHOPEE_INTEGRATION=true
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ENABLE_CAMERA_SCANNER=true

# ============================================
# OPTIONAL - Supabase (if using)
# ============================================

# Get from: https://supabase.com → Project Settings → API
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxxx.supabase.co
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# ============================================
# HOW TO ADD THESE IN VERCEL
# ============================================
#
# Method 1: During Initial Import
# 1. When importing project, click "Environment Variables"
# 2. Add NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL with your Render URL
# 3. Click "Deploy"
#
# Method 2: After Deployment
# 1. Go to: https://vercel.com/[your-project]/settings/environment-variables
# 2. Click "Add New"
# 3. Name: NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL
# 4. Value: Your Render backend URL
# 5. Environment: Production (and Preview if needed)
# 6. Click "Save"
# 7. Redeploy: Deployments → ⋯ → "Redeploy"
#
# ============================================
# IMPORTANT NOTES
# ============================================
#
# 1. All variables starting with NEXT_PUBLIC_ are exposed to the browser
# 2. NEVER put sensitive secrets in NEXT_PUBLIC_ variables
# 3. Backend URL must NOT have trailing slash
# 4. Changes require redeployment to take effect
# 5. Vercel automatically includes NODE_ENV=production
#
# ============================================
# VERCEL DASHBOARD QUICK LINKS
# ============================================
#
# Environment Variables:
# https://vercel.com/[your-project]/settings/environment-variables
#
# Deployments:
# https://vercel.com/[your-project]/deployments
#
# Domains:
# https://vercel.com/[your-project]/settings/domains
#
# Analytics:
# https://vercel.com/[your-project]/analytics
#
# ============================================
# TESTING YOUR SETUP
# ============================================
#
# After deployment, test:
# 1. Open your Vercel URL
# 2. Open browser console (F12)
# 3. Check for errors
# 4. Verify API calls go to correct backend URL
# 5. Test login functionality
#
# If you see CORS errors:
# - Check ALLOWED_ORIGINS in Render backend
# - Make sure it includes your Vercel URL
# - No trailing slashes in either URL
#
# ============================================
